ce:section.ce:para:
To investigate the transport phenomenon through tracer test at varying distance from the injection and acquiring point, spatial information in heterogeneous media needs to be acquired [56,57]. Test were conducted which may reveal the subsurface information. At an experimental site in granite terrain, PSS-CQD tracer was used for groundwater velocity estimation through multiwall technique under induced condition. The experimental site was selected in such a way that the cluster wells (Table 2
                        ) in the study area should connected with micro and major fracture from end to end between injection well and acquiring well, so that the performance of new CQD tracer could be justified. The experiment was carried out to test and evaluate CQD as water tracer for groundwater flow studies. The site is at a distance of about 30 km from Hyderabad and is located near to Maheshwaram town in Rangareddy district of Telangana State of India (Fig. 9
                         & Supplementary Fig. S8). The site area is in granite terrain where multiple bore wells of 6″ diameter were drilled up to maximum depth of 50 m to study hydrology of Maheshwaram watershed. Lithological studies shows that the formation up to the depth of 45 m is characterized by weathered and fracture formations. The bore hole test was conducted under induced condition where in, the observation well was pumped continuously using 1 HP submerssible pump for creating hydraulic gradient for inducing groundwater flow and also for sample collection of the aquifer water. The details are as follows;
